President Uhuru Kenyatta has sent a message of condolence to King Mswati III and the people of Eswatini following the death of Prime Minister Ambrose Mandvulo Dlamini.
The 52-year-old PM died while being treated for Covid-19 at a hospital in South Africa.
In a message of encouragement and comfort to King Mswati, President Kenyatta said Kenya stands with the people of Eswatini as they mourn their departed leader.



