“Prime Minister Dlamini was an industrious and devoted leader who was committed to improving the wellbeing of his fellow countrymen. It is unfortunate that we have lost such a great leader at a time like this,” he said on Monday.
“We will forever cherish his contribution to human development, especially in the banking and telecommunication sectors, where he served successfully for many years before becoming Prime Minister.”



